{"name":"Mesmerist","type":"class","effects":[],"system":{"description":{"gm":"","value":"<p>As a mesmerist, you leverage your connection with another plane to influence the minds of others. Your spellcasting is versatile and subtle, relying on suggestion and manipulation.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Ability: CHARISMA</strong></p>\n<p>At 1st level, your class gives you an ability boost to Charisma.</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Points: 8 plus your Constitution modifier</strong></p>\n<p>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at 1st level and every level thereafter.</p>\n<h1>Roleplaying the Mesmerist</h1>\n<h2>During Combat Encounters...</h2>\n<p>By exerting your mind’s dominance, you vex your foes and shore up your allies’ defenses.</p>\n<h2>During Social Encounters...</h2>\n<p>You charm, deceive, and distract others to advance your social standing and obtain access to guarded information.</p>\n<h2>While Exploring...</h2>\n<p>You comfort your allies’ wounds and subconsciously prepare them for danger.</p>\n<h2>In Downtime...</h2>\n<p>You assess potential foes and plan how to win the fight against them before it begins. You send your mind out to the planes to gather strength.</p>\n<h2>You Might...</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Adopt a guise to hide your mental powers or openly flaunt your mind’s superiority. </li>\n<li>Take up employment as an entertainer, counselor, advisor, or scam artist. </li>\n<li>Eagerly reach out to your planar connection or consider this connection a grim necessity.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Others Probably...</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Find your insights fascinating and terrifying. </li>\n<li>Attempt to keep secrets from you. This is a often futile effort. </li>\n<li>Wonder how you’re influencing them right now.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Initial Proficiencies</h1>\n<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>\n<h2>Perception</h2>\n<p>Expert in Perception</p>\n<h2>Saving Throws</h2>\n<p>Trained in Fortitude</p>\n<p>Trained in Reflex</p>\n<p>Expert in Will</p>\n<h2>Skills</h2>\n<p>Trained in Occultism</p>\n<p>Trained in one skill determined by your knack</p>\n<p>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 4 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>\n<h2>Attacks</h2>\n<p>Trained in simple weapons</p>\n<p>Trained in unarmed attacks</p>\n<h2>Defenses</h2>\n<p>Trained in light armor</p>\n<p>Trained in unarmored defense</p>\n<h2>Spells</h2>\n<p>Trained in occult spell attacks</p>\n<p>Trained in occult spell DCs</p>\n<h1>Class Features</h1>\n<p>You gain these abilities as a mesmerist. Abilities granted at higher levels list the level at which you gain them next to the features’ names.</p>\n<table class=\"pf2-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Your Level</th>\n<th>Class Features</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Ancestry and background, initial proficiencies, knack, occult spellcasting, planar connection, spell repertoire</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>2nd-level spells, general feat, lightning reflexes, signature spells, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>3rd-level spells, ability boosts, ancestry feat, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>4th-level spells, expert spellcaster, general feat, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>5th-level spells, ancestry feat, great fortitude, resolve, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>Ability boosts, Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11</td>\n<td>6th-level spells, mesmerist weapon expertise, general feat, skill increase, vigilant senses</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13</td>\n<td>7th-level spells, ancestry feat, light armor expertise, skill increase, weapon specialization</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15</td>\n<td>8th-level spells, ability boosts, general feat, master spellcaster, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>16</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>17</td>\n<td>9th-level spells, ancestry feat, greater resolve, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>18</td>\n<td>Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>19</td>\n<td>General feat, legendary spellcaster, mental paragon, skill increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>20</td>\n<td>Ability boosts, Mesmerist feat, skill feat</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Ancestry and Background</h2>\n<p>In addition to the abilities provided by your class at 1st level, you have the benefits of your selected ancestry and background.</p>\n<h2>Knack and Planar Connection</h2>\n<p>As a mesmerist, your mind connects with another plane, and you leverage this connection in a set of practices over others’ minds. Choose a knack and a planar connection.</p>\n<h3>Knacks</h3>\n<p>At 1st level, choose a knack, representing how you use your mesmerism. Your knack grants you a Cue, a Stare, or a Treatment. You also become trained in the listed skill at 1st level.</p>\n<p>Knacks can be found here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.HoLcOjHYOlpPnfKJ]{Delver}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.w4gRMSwFUSBbRwt5]{Hypnotherapist}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.Zz2LTsDY1JPBX026]{Illusior}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.ja5BiknKmanKWe4M]{Manipulator}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.UA9ppuFIcYQ0cdtt]{Stage Hypnotist}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.XPYTw9VXlG6XojTJ]{Supremum}</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>Planar Connections</h3>\n<p>You draw your magic from a plane that your mind is intrinsically connected to. Choose one of the following planes as your planar connection. You learn the listed Cue, Stare, or Treatment, and add each granted spell to your repertoire as an occult spell when you gain this spell level. If your knack and your planar connection grant you the same 1st- level Cue, Stare, or Treatment, you may choose another. You gain the planar essence benefit if you take the Planar Essence mesmerist class feat.</p>\n<p>Planar Connections can be found here:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.LMipwdeZwdk2LM1Z]{Abaddon, Abyss, or Hell}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.ibJUF0jII7fEu0AT]{Astral Plane}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.qenB2iBxX2idh6Wb]{Axis}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.QnCErGLJUgulH5Hx]{Dimension of Time or Ethereal Plane}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.CgFQZ79BXOVNppSk]{Dreamlands or Leng}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.w5untdq2QAyLV3OB]{Elysium, Heaven, or Nirvana}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.5c2x5AF16fuyVqTd]{First World or Positive Energy Plane}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.LPiwHHhIumEdke3n]{Maelstrom}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.LRz5gEMrdHWHgvLL]{Material Plane}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.YwYeXiM34ke5E6j6]{Plane of Air, Earth, Fire, or Water}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.Vt4EHMJTMMatL1NQ]{Plane of Shadow or Negative Energy Plane}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.SbscFrVHpf4NnQ4y]{The Boneyard}</li>\n<li>@UUID[Compendium.frontiers-of-magic.frontiers-of-the-mind-featfeatures.QrhVSaC7GYsh726a]{The Dark Tapestry}</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Occult Spellcasting</h2>\n<p>You draw upon magic from your planar connection. You can cast occult spells using the Cast a Spell activity, and you can supply material, somatic, and verbal components when casting spells. Because you’re a mesmerist, you can usually focus on the mind of your target for spells requiring material components. If your spell targets a creature, you don’t need a material component pouch or another hand free.</p>\n<p>Each day, you can cast up to two 1st-level spells. You must know spells to cast them, and you learn them via the spell repertoire class feature. The number of spells you can cast each day is called your spell slots.</p>\n<p>As you increase in level as a mesmerist, your number of spells per day increases, as does the highest level of spells you can cast, as shown on Table 1: Mesmerist Spells per Day.</p>\n<p>Some of your spells require you to attempt a spell attack roll to see how effective they are, or have your enemies roll against your spell DC (typically by attempting a saving throw). Since your key ability is Charisma, your spell attack rolls and spell DCs use your Charisma modifier.</p>\n<h3><strong>Heightening Spells</strong></h3>\n<p>When you get spell slots of 2nd level and higher, you can fill those slots with stronger versions of lower-level spells. This increases the spell’s level to match the spell slot. You must have a spell in your spell repertoire at the level you want to cast in order to heighten it to that level. Many spells have specific improvements when they are heightened to certain levels. The signature spells class feature lets you heighten certain spells freely.</p>\n<h3><strong>Cantrips</strong></h3>\n<p>Some of your spells are cantrips. A cantrip is a special type of spell that doesn’t use spell slots. You can cast a cantrip at will, any number of times per day. A cantrip is automatically heightened to half your level rounded up—this is usually equal to the highest level of bard spell slot you have. For example, as a 1st-level mesmerist, your cantrips are 1st-level spells, and as a 5th-level mesmerist, your cantrips are 3rd-level spells.</p>\n<h3>Manipulation Spells</h3>\n<p>As a mesmerist, you learn three manipulation spells: implant cue, mesmerist stare, and touch treatment.<br />Manipulation spells are a type of focus spell. It costs 1 Focus Point to cast a focus spell, and you start with a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to study another creature’s mind, plumb the depths of your own mind, or psychically connect to your plane.</p>\n<p>Focus spells are automatically heightened to half your level rounded up, much like cantrips. Focus spells don't require spell slots, and you can’t cast them using spell slots. Taking feats can give you more focus spells and increase the size of your focus pool, though your focus pool can never hold more than 3 Focus Points.</p>\n<p>Your three manipulation spells use Cues (implant cue), Stares (mesmerist stare), and Touches (touch treatment). You learn one Cue, Stare, or Touch from your knack and one from your planar connection. You can learn others from mesmerist class feats. Your Cues, Stares, and Touches heighten to the same level as your manipulation spells.</p>\n<table class=\"pf2-table\" style=\"width:100%;height:638px\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height:29px\">\n<th style=\"width:13.14%;height:29px\">Your Level</th>\n<th style=\"width:11.7885%;height:29px\">Cantrips</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.18645%;height:29px\">1st</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.70263%;height:29px\">2nd</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.39049%;height:29px\">3rd</th>\n<th style=\"width:7.37828%;height:29px\">4th</th>\n<th style=\